{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0155fuBK9qQegS1fcVcrMhgr","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Migration Summary: API Envelope Contract\n\nHere are the current API consumption patterns for the three waitlist clients, plus the reference pattern already implemented in telegram:\n\n---\n\n### **1. `/waitlist/src/lib/auth-api.ts`**\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `POST /auth/challenge` → `ChallengeResponse` (nonce, message, expiresAt)\n- `POST /auth/verify` → `VerifyResponse` (accessToken, refreshToken + expiry)\n- `POST /auth/refresh` → `RefreshResponse` (tokens)\n- `POST /auth/logout` → void\n\n**Current Response Parsing** (auth-api.ts:29–39):\n```typescript\nasync function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n  const json = await res.json();\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    const msg = typeof json?.error === \"string\" ? json.error : `Auth request failed (${res.status})`;\n    throw new Error(msg);\n  }\n  return json as T;\n}\n```\n\n**Error Shape Expected:** `{ error: string }` on non-2xx  \n**Status Branching:** None (only checks `res.ok`)\n\n---\n\n### **2. `/waitlist/src/lib/referral-api.ts`**\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /public-referral/code/{code}` → `{ exists: boolean }` (no auth)\n- `POST /referral/code` → `ReferralCodeResponse` (code)\n- `GET /referral/code` → `ReferralCodeResponse`\n- `POST /referral/apply` → `ApplyReferralResponse` (referrerUserId, benefit)\n- `GET /referral/referrer` → `ReferrerResponse`\n- `GET /referral/stats` → `ReferralStatsResponse`\n- `GET /referral/referrals` → `{ items: WaitlistReferral[] }`\n\n**Current Response Parsing** (referral-api.ts:44–57):\n```typescript\nasync function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n  const json = await res.json();\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    const err = json?.error;\n    const msg = typeof err === \"string\" ? err : typeof err?.message === \"string\" ? err.message : `Request failed (${res.status})`;\n    throw new Error(msg);\n  }\n  return json as T;\n}\n```\n\n**Error Shape Expected:** `{ error: string | { message: string } }`  \n**Status Branching:** None\n\n---\n\n### **3. `/waitlist/src/components/TelegramCard.tsx`**\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /telegram/generate-link` (probes and generates)\n\n**Current Response Parsing** (TelegramCard.tsx:48–67, 85–100):\n```typescript\nconst res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/telegram/generate-link`, { ... });\nif (!res.ok) throw new Error(\"Failed\");\nconst data = await res.json();\nif (data.alreadyLinked) { ... } else { ... }\nif (data.deepLink) window.open(data.deepLink, \"_blank\");\n```\n\n**Error Shape Expected:** None explicitly—relies on `res.ok` check  \n**Status Branching:** Response-data branching on `alreadyLinked` boolean and optional `deepLink`\n\n---\n\n### **4. `/telegram/src/backend-client.ts` (ALREADY MIGRATED)**\n\n**Reference Implementation** — The migration pattern to follow:\n\n**New Envelope Interfaces** (backend-client.ts:30–45):\n```typescript\ninterface ApiEnvelopeSuccess<T> {\n  ok: true;\n  data: T;\n}\n\ninterface ApiEnvelopeError {\n  ok: false;\n  error: { code: string; message: string; retryable?: boolean; details?: unknown };\n}\n\ntype ApiEnvelope<T> = ApiEnvelopeSuccess<T> | ApiEnvelopeError;\n```\n\n**Parsing Logic** (backend-client.ts:89–111):\n- Calls `response.json()`\n- Guards with `isEnvelope<T>()` type check\n- On parse failure or missing envelope → logs error, returns `null`\n- Returns the full envelope, caller extracts `envelope.data` on success or switches on `envelope.error.code`\n\n**Error Handling Pattern** (e.g., backend-client.ts:156–174):\n```typescript\nif (envelope.ok) {\n  return { ok: true, ...envelope.data };\n}\nswitch (envelope.error.code) {\n  case \"TELEGRAM_ALREADY_LINKED\": return { ok: false, error: \"TELEGRAM_ALREADY_LINKED\" };\n  case \"TELEGRAM_TOKEN_EXPIRED\": return { ok: false, error: \"TOKEN_NOT_FOUND\" };\n  default: return { ok: false, error: \"UNKNOWN\" };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Migration Checklist for waitlist clients:**\n\n1. **auth-api.ts & referral-api.ts:** Replace string-based error extraction with envelope unpacking. Extract actual data from `envelope.data` on success path; switch on `envelope.error.code` for known error codes; map to typed result objects.\n\n2. **TelegramCard.tsx:** Wrap endpoint calls with envelope guard. Check `data.ok` (not just `res.ok`). Extract data from `data.data` structure; handle error codes explicitly.\n\n3. **Reference:** Use telegram backend-client.ts (lines 89–175) as the pattern for error handling, type safety, and logging."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3be46b6c-3354-4668-9b8a-f4306801d133","uuid":"d46bd6af-b325-4182-abcd-a01a728d1d1e","timestamp":"2026-04-22T11:16:13.119Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to document how three clients need to migrate to consume the new API envelope contract from backend. Read and summarize the CURRENT (pre-migration) state of these files:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/waitlist/src/lib/auth-api.ts`\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/waitlist/src/lib/referral-api.ts`\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/waitlist/src/components/TelegramCard.tsx`\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/telegram/src/backend-client.ts` (ALREADY migrated — note what changed)\n\nFor each file, report:\n- What endpoints it calls\n- The current response parsing logic (how it extracts success data and errors)\n- What error shapes it currently expects\n- Any status-based branching\n\nFor the telegram backend-client, note that it's already migrated — document the before → after pattern used there (it's a good reference for the migration doc).\n\nReport concisely — quote key snippets but keep your summary under 600 words. Use file_path:line_number for key code locations.","agentId":"a3157c0017393a6d5","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Migration Summary: API Envelope Contract\n\nHere are the current API consumption patterns for the three waitlist clients, plus the reference pattern already implemented in telegram:\n\n---\n\n### **1. `/waitlist/src/lib/auth-api.ts`**\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `POST /auth/challenge` → `ChallengeResponse` (nonce, message, expiresAt)\n- `POST /auth/verify` → `VerifyResponse` (accessToken, refreshToken + expiry)\n- `POST /auth/refresh` → `RefreshResponse` (tokens)\n- `POST /auth/logout` → void\n\n**Current Response Parsing** (auth-api.ts:29–39):\n```typescript\nasync function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n  const json = await res.json();\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    const msg = typeof json?.error === \"string\" ? json.error : `Auth request failed (${res.status})`;\n    throw new Error(msg);\n  }\n  return json as T;\n}\n```\n\n**Error Shape Expected:** `{ error: string }` on non-2xx  \n**Status Branching:** None (only checks `res.ok`)\n\n---\n\n### **2. `/waitlist/src/lib/referral-api.ts`**\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `GET /public-referral/code/{code}` → `{ exists: boolean }` (no auth)\n- `POST /referral/code` → `ReferralCodeResponse` (code)\n- `GET /referral/code` → `ReferralCodeResponse`\n- `POST /referral/apply` → `ApplyReferralResponse` (referrerUserId, benefit)\n- `GET /referral/referrer` → `ReferrerResponse`\n- `GET /referral/stats` → `ReferralStatsResponse`\n- `GET /referral/referrals` → `{ items: WaitlistReferral[] }`\n\n**Current Response Parsing** (referral-api.ts:44–57):\n```typescript\nasync function parseResponse<T>(res: Response): Promise<T> {\n  const json = await res.json();\n  if (!res.ok) {\n    const err = json?.error;\n    const msg = typeof err === \"string\" ? err : typeof err?.message === \"string\" ? err.message : `Request failed (${res.status})`;\n    throw new Error(msg);\n  }\n  return json as T;\n}\n```\n\n**Error Shape Expected:** `{ error: string | { message: string } }`  \n**Status Branching:** None\n\n---\n\n### **3. `/waitlist/src/components/TelegramCard.tsx`**\n\n**Endpoint:** `POST /telegram/generate-link` (probes and generates)\n\n**Current Response Parsing** (TelegramCard.tsx:48–67, 85–100):\n```typescript\nconst res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}/telegram/generate-link`, { ... });\nif (!res.ok) throw new Error(\"Failed\");\nconst data = await res.json();\nif (data.alreadyLinked) { ... } else { ... }\nif (data.deepLink) window.open(data.deepLink, \"_blank\");\n```\n\n**Error Shape Expected:** None explicitly—relies on `res.ok` check  \n**Status Branching:** Response-data branching on `alreadyLinked` boolean and optional `deepLink`\n\n---\n\n### **4. `/telegram/src/backend-client.ts` (ALREADY MIGRATED)**\n\n**Reference Implementation** — The migration pattern to follow:\n\n**New Envelope Interfaces** (backend-client.ts:30–45):\n```typescript\ninterface ApiEnvelopeSuccess<T> {\n  ok: true;\n  data: T;\n}\n\ninterface ApiEnvelopeError {\n  ok: false;\n  error: { code: string; message: string; retryable?: boolean; details?: unknown };\n}\n\ntype ApiEnvelope<T> = ApiEnvelopeSuccess<T> | ApiEnvelopeError;\n```\n\n**Parsing Logic** (backend-client.ts:89–111):\n- Calls `response.json()`\n- Guards with `isEnvelope<T>()` type check\n- On parse failure or missing envelope → logs error, returns `null`\n- Returns the full envelope, caller extracts `envelope.data` on success or switches on `envelope.error.code`\n\n**Error Handling Pattern** (e.g., backend-client.ts:156–174):\n```typescript\nif (envelope.ok) {\n  return { ok: true, ...envelope.data };\n}\nswitch (envelope.error.code) {\n  case \"TELEGRAM_ALREADY_LINKED\": return { ok: false, error: \"TELEGRAM_ALREADY_LINKED\" };\n  case \"TELEGRAM_TOKEN_EXPIRED\": return { ok: false, error: \"TOKEN_NOT_FOUND\" };\n  default: return { ok: false, error: \"UNKNOWN\" };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Migration Checklist for waitlist clients:**\n\n1. **auth-api.ts & referral-api.ts:** Replace string-based error extraction with envelope unpacking. Extract actual data from `envelope.data` on success path; switch on `envelope.error.code` for known error codes; map to typed result objects.\n\n2. **TelegramCard.tsx:** Wrap endpoint calls with envelope guard. Check `data.ok` (not just `res.ok`). Extract data from `data.data` structure; handle error codes explicitly.\n\n3. **Reference:** Use telegram backend-client.ts (lines 89–175) as the pattern for error handling, type safety, and logging."}],"totalDurationMs":14441,"totalTokens":42576,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12274,"cache_read_input_tokens":28933,"output_tokens":1362,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":12274},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":7,"output_tokens":1362,"cache_read_input_tokens":28933,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12274,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":12274,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":4,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":0,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
