{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MLNKwYiohLHyJ2yoB3QiUR","type":"tool_result","content":"1\timport { getAccessToken } from \"@/lib/auth/store\";\n2\t\n3\tconst rawBackendUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL as\n4\t  | string\n5\t  | undefined;\n6\t\n7\tif (!rawBackendUrl) {\n8\t  throw new Error(\"Missing required VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL\");\n9\t}\n10\t\n11\texport const BACKEND_URL = rawBackendUrl.replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n12\t\n13\texport class ApiError extends Error {\n14\t  constructor(\n15\t    message: string,\n16\t    public status: number,\n17\t  ) {\n18\t    super(message);\n19\t  }\n20\t}\n21\t\n22\texport function authHeaders(): HeadersInit {\n23\t  const token = getAccessToken();\n24\t  return {\n25\t    \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n26\t    ...(token ? { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` } : {}),\n27\t  };\n28\t}\n29\t\n30\texport async function authFetch<T>(\n31\t  path: string,\n32\t  init?: RequestInit,\n33\t): Promise<T> {\n34\t  const res = await fetch(`${BACKEND_URL}${path}`, {\n35\t    ...init,\n36\t    headers: { ...authHeaders(), ...init?.headers },\n37\t  });\n38\t  if (!res.ok) {\n39\t    const body = await res.json().catch(() => ({}));\n40\t    throw new ApiError(\n41\t      (body as { error?: string }).error ?? `HTTP ${res.status}`,\n42\t      res.status,\n43\t    );\n44\t  }\n45\t  return res.json() as Promise<T>;\n46\t}\n47\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01E5hECb4PxMbsEvCF4MW2iD","session_id":"3be46b6c-3354-4668-9b8a-f4306801d133","uuid":"122eb9db-d7c9-44b6-aa29-100ef44ff3cb","timestamp":"2026-04-22T11:16:23.239Z"}
