{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E5hECb4PxMbsEvCF4MW2iD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Migration Summary: Current API Envelope Contract\n\n### 1. **Main API Client** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/api.ts`)\n\n**Endpoints covered:** All authenticated endpoints  \n**Error class:**\n```typescript\nexport class ApiError extends Error {\n  constructor(message: string, public status: number) { super(message); }\n}\n```\n\n**Current parsing logic (lines 30–46):**\n- Checks `res.ok`; if false, attempts to parse response JSON\n- Extracts error message from `{ error?: string }` field, falls back to `HTTP ${status}`\n- Throws `ApiError(message, status)` on non-2xx responses\n- On success (res.ok), directly returns `res.json()` as type `<T>`\n\n**Status-based branching:** None — all non-2xx responses throw uniformly; higher-level code must check `err.status` if needed.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Auth API Client** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/auth/api.ts`)\n\n**Endpoints covered:** `/auth/challenge`, `/auth/verify`, `/auth/refresh`, `/auth/logout`  \n**Response shapes:**\n```typescript\ninterface ChallengeResponse { nonce: string; message: string; expiresAt: string; }\ninterface VerifyResponse { accessToken: string; accessExpiresAt: string; refreshToken: string; refreshExpiresAt: string; }\ninterface RefreshResponse { ... same as VerifyResponse }\n```\n\n**Current parsing logic (lines 35–42):**\n- Custom `parseResponse<T>()` reads full JSON first\n- If `!res.ok`, checks `json?.error` (string), throws plain `Error(msg)` with status in message\n- Returns parsed json directly as type `<T>`\n\n**Status-based branching:** None explicit; error message includes status, but no special handling by status code.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Transaction Error Parser** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/parse-transaction-error.ts`)\n\n**Surfaces:** Solana on-chain transaction errors (wallet rejection, insufficient lamports, simulation failure, network errors)  \n**Backend error detection (lines 60–80):**\n```typescript\nfunction checkBackendRequestError(err: unknown): string | null {\n  if (typeof err === \"object\" && err !== null && \"status\" in err && \"message\" in err) {\n    const status = (err as { status: number }).status;\n    const message = (err as { message: string }).message;\n    if (status === 401) return \"Backend authentication failed...\";\n    if (status === 409) return \"Action failed due to a conflict...\";\n    if (status === 429) return \"Too many attempts...\";\n    return message;\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\n**Consumes:** Checks for objects with `{ status: number, message: string }` (matches `ApiError` interface). Status-based branching: **401, 409, 429** are handled specially; others fallback to message. Otherwise, treats error as Solana tx error (string matching).\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Profile Data Fetching** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/pages/profile/profile-data.ts`)\n\n**Endpoints covered:** `/profile/transactions`, `/price/sol-usd`, `/referral/code`, `/referral/referrer`, `/referral/stats`, `/referral/apply`  \n**Usage of ApiError (lines 99, 127):**\n```typescript\nif (err instanceof ApiError && err.status === 404) return null;\n```\n\n**Current patterns:**\n- Most calls via `authFetch<T>()` (lines 55–57, 97, 112, 125, 140, 152)\n- **404 handling only:** referral code and referrer queries catch 404 and return null (expected not-found state)\n- `/price/sol-usd` bypasses `authFetch`, uses raw fetch with simple `res.ok` check (lines 80–82)\n\n---\n\n## Migration Points\n\n**Current contract:**\n- Success: response body directly is the payload (no envelope)\n- Error: `{ error?: string }` at root; thrown as `ApiError(message, status)`\n- Backend errors in transaction parser expect `{ status, message }` structure\n\n**New API contract** (to be implemented):\n- Likely: `{ success: boolean; data?: T; error?: { code: string; message: string } }`\n- Implications: All callers using `authFetch<T>` must handle envelope unwrapping; transaction error parser must adapt to new error structure; 404 checks need validation against new error code field."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3be46b6c-3354-4668-9b8a-f4306801d133","uuid":"ca9a900f-6243-4743-932f-78a916d5a61f","timestamp":"2026-04-22T11:16:37.040Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to document how webapp needs to migrate to consume the new API envelope contract from backend. Read and summarize the CURRENT state of these files:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/api.ts` (main API client — how does it parse success/error, what error class does it throw, does it have status-based branching?)\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/auth/api.ts` (auth-specific client)\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/parse-transaction-error.ts` (error parser for on-chain tx errors — does this consume backend errors or Solana errors?)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/pages/profile/profile-data.ts` (profile data fetching)\n\nFor each file, report concisely:\n- What endpoints or surfaces it covers\n- The current response parsing logic (quote key snippets, <30 lines)\n- What error shapes/types it expects\n- Any status-based branching (e.g. \"handles 401 separately\")\n- If there's a shared ApiError class, quote its interface\n\nReport under 800 words, using file_path:line_number for code locations. The webapp repo is read-only to us — I'm only documenting the migration, not implementing it.","agentId":"a9412229e7966f4fc","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Migration Summary: Current API Envelope Contract\n\n### 1. **Main API Client** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/api.ts`)\n\n**Endpoints covered:** All authenticated endpoints  \n**Error class:**\n```typescript\nexport class ApiError extends Error {\n  constructor(message: string, public status: number) { super(message); }\n}\n```\n\n**Current parsing logic (lines 30–46):**\n- Checks `res.ok`; if false, attempts to parse response JSON\n- Extracts error message from `{ error?: string }` field, falls back to `HTTP ${status}`\n- Throws `ApiError(message, status)` on non-2xx responses\n- On success (res.ok), directly returns `res.json()` as type `<T>`\n\n**Status-based branching:** None — all non-2xx responses throw uniformly; higher-level code must check `err.status` if needed.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Auth API Client** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/auth/api.ts`)\n\n**Endpoints covered:** `/auth/challenge`, `/auth/verify`, `/auth/refresh`, `/auth/logout`  \n**Response shapes:**\n```typescript\ninterface ChallengeResponse { nonce: string; message: string; expiresAt: string; }\ninterface VerifyResponse { accessToken: string; accessExpiresAt: string; refreshToken: string; refreshExpiresAt: string; }\ninterface RefreshResponse { ... same as VerifyResponse }\n```\n\n**Current parsing logic (lines 35–42):**\n- Custom `parseResponse<T>()` reads full JSON first\n- If `!res.ok`, checks `json?.error` (string), throws plain `Error(msg)` with status in message\n- Returns parsed json directly as type `<T>`\n\n**Status-based branching:** None explicit; error message includes status, but no special handling by status code.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Transaction Error Parser** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/lib/parse-transaction-error.ts`)\n\n**Surfaces:** Solana on-chain transaction errors (wallet rejection, insufficient lamports, simulation failure, network errors)  \n**Backend error detection (lines 60–80):**\n```typescript\nfunction checkBackendRequestError(err: unknown): string | null {\n  if (typeof err === \"object\" && err !== null && \"status\" in err && \"message\" in err) {\n    const status = (err as { status: number }).status;\n    const message = (err as { message: string }).message;\n    if (status === 401) return \"Backend authentication failed...\";\n    if (status === 409) return \"Action failed due to a conflict...\";\n    if (status === 429) return \"Too many attempts...\";\n    return message;\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\n**Consumes:** Checks for objects with `{ status: number, message: string }` (matches `ApiError` interface). Status-based branching: **401, 409, 429** are handled specially; others fallback to message. Otherwise, treats error as Solana tx error (string matching).\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Profile Data Fetching** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/webapp/src/pages/profile/profile-data.ts`)\n\n**Endpoints covered:** `/profile/transactions`, `/price/sol-usd`, `/referral/code`, `/referral/referrer`, `/referral/stats`, `/referral/apply`  \n**Usage of ApiError (lines 99, 127):**\n```typescript\nif (err instanceof ApiError && err.status === 404) return null;\n```\n\n**Current patterns:**\n- Most calls via `authFetch<T>()` (lines 55–57, 97, 112, 125, 140, 152)\n- **404 handling only:** referral code and referrer queries catch 404 and return null (expected not-found state)\n- `/price/sol-usd` bypasses `authFetch`, uses raw fetch with simple `res.ok` check (lines 80–82)\n\n---\n\n## Migration Points\n\n**Current contract:**\n- Success: response body directly is the payload (no envelope)\n- Error: `{ error?: string }` at root; thrown as `ApiError(message, status)`\n- Backend errors in transaction parser expect `{ status, message }` structure\n\n**New API contract** (to be implemented):\n- Likely: `{ success: boolean; data?: T; error?: { code: string; message: string } }`\n- Implications: All callers using `authFetch<T>` must handle envelope unwrapping; transaction error parser must adapt to new error structure; 404 checks need validation against new error code field."}],"totalDurationMs":15038,"totalTokens":37861,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8474,"cache_read_input_tokens":28244,"output_tokens":1136,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h